## ðŸ’¬ Problem Statement

Given a string `s` in **Roman numeral format**, your task is to convert it into an **integer**.

Roman symbols and their values:

| Symbol | Value |
| ------ | ----- |
| I      | 1     |
| V      | 5     |
| X      | 10    |
| L      | 50    |
| C      | 100   |
| D      | 500   |
| M      | 1000  |

> **Rule**:
> If a smaller value appears **before** a larger one (like `IV`), subtract it.
> Else, add it.

